WEBVTT

00:00:01.930 --> 00:00:04.940
And down this goes.

00:00:05.410 --> 00:00:07.400
Whew! I'm exhausted.

00:00:07.400 --> 00:00:08.610
Hey, honey!

00:00:08.610 --> 00:00:10.400
Whoa, what is it? You don't need to shout.

00:00:10.400 --> 00:00:13.010
Quiet! Just get over here!

00:00:14.610 --> 00:00:16.450
Good grief. What now?

00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:21.350
Kita-chan?!

00:00:38.390 --> 00:00:48.730
Umamusume

00:00:42.270 --> 00:00:48.730
Pretty Derby

00:01:52.520 --> 00:01:56.530
Episode 12
\hKitasan Black

00:01:52.970 --> 00:01:56.780
Thank you all for coming today.

00:01:58.630 --> 00:02:02.360
I asked my trainer to arrange this
so that I can announce

00:02:02.360 --> 00:02:04.140
a decision that I've recently made.

00:02:06.040 --> 00:02:10.960
I, Kitasan Black, after finishing
my races at the end of this year,

00:02:10.960 --> 00:02:13.070
will be retiring from the Twinkle Series.

00:02:14.690 --> 00:02:19.480
It's my belief that I've run in a lot
of races without any major injuries.

00:02:19.950 --> 00:02:24.700
No matter how much I practiced, or how much
I raced, I never seemed to get exhausted.

00:02:25.710 --> 00:02:30.230
But recently, at the Fall Tennoushou,
I could feel it clearly.

00:02:30.230 --> 00:02:33.780
My body is no longer at its peak.

00:02:34.880 --> 00:02:40.260
I believe I'll only be able to run to my
satisfaction until the end of this year,

00:02:40.260 --> 00:02:42.210
which is what led me to this decision.

00:02:42.640 --> 00:02:46.320
Do you have any comments on your
race schedule for the future?

00:02:46.320 --> 00:02:49.940
I'm going to enter the Japan Cup. And then...

00:02:51.070 --> 00:02:54.020
My last run will be at the Arima Kinen.

00:02:55.700 --> 00:02:58.440
I intend to give everything
that I have left so that these

00:02:58.440 --> 00:03:01.450
will be great races that I won't regret.

00:03:01.930 --> 00:03:04.950
I hope you'll watch until the end.

00:03:06.150 --> 00:03:09.860
But why?! She won the Fall Tennoushou!

00:03:09.860 --> 00:03:12.300
There are things that only
the person running can feel.

00:03:12.300 --> 00:03:15.850
Kita-chan must've felt something like that.

00:03:16.230 --> 00:03:19.870
Choosing her moment to step out of
the spotlight and announcing it...

00:03:20.790 --> 00:03:25.740
But in spite of that, she makes an attempt
to conquer the Fall Senior Triple Crown

00:03:25.740 --> 00:03:29.980
in an effort to solidify her
legacy as the strongest.

00:03:29.980 --> 00:03:33.050
Whether it was intentional or not,

00:03:33.050 --> 00:03:36.360
she has a knack for putting her
most charismatic face forward.

00:03:36.360 --> 00:03:41.220
I think this might call for paying more than
a little attention to how she runs

00:03:36.880 --> 00:03:41.880
R
o
y
c
e

00:03:41.220 --> 00:03:43.860
until the very end.

00:03:46.080 --> 00:03:47.510
I see.

00:03:47.870 --> 00:03:51.370
Everyone, thank you so much.

00:03:51.600 --> 00:03:53.980
Don't sweat it. It was the least we could do.

00:03:53.980 --> 00:03:55.080
Kita-san!

00:03:55.080 --> 00:03:57.130
Come on, Spe-chan, don't cry.

00:03:57.570 --> 00:04:00.660
Dia-chan, thanks for coming.

00:04:00.660 --> 00:04:03.260
It's okay. Don't mention it.

00:04:03.260 --> 00:04:07.360
Starting tomorrow, we'll resume
your training for the Japan Cup.

00:04:07.360 --> 00:04:11.520
Right. Please make it more
intense than ever before.

00:04:11.990 --> 00:04:13.450
I don't know...

00:04:13.450 --> 00:04:14.610
I've made up my mind.

00:04:14.610 --> 00:04:18.510
I want to put everything I have
into my last races. So, please...

00:04:19.760 --> 00:04:20.780
Understood.

00:04:21.050 --> 00:04:22.590
Thank you so much.

00:04:28.050 --> 00:04:29.160
Cheval!

00:04:31.740 --> 00:04:34.010
Did you see Kitasan's announcement?

00:04:34.630 --> 00:04:36.740
Yeah, part of it.

00:04:37.160 --> 00:04:38.240
I see.

00:04:40.050 --> 00:04:43.630
I'm going to miss her. We've been
together all this time.

00:04:48.950 --> 00:04:50.580
Miss her?

00:04:51.480 --> 00:04:54.480
H
i
s
h
i

00:04:57.690 --> 00:04:58.540
Groovy Sis...

00:04:58.540 --> 00:05:00.270
Don't call me that!

00:05:01.100 --> 00:05:02.250
Well, it's fine.

00:05:02.640 --> 00:05:05.880
More importantly, you need to
maintain focus during training.

00:05:05.880 --> 00:05:07.490
Otherwise you could unexpectedly get injured.

00:05:08.890 --> 00:05:11.460
Is Kitasan's press conference bothering you?

00:05:11.840 --> 00:05:12.870
It is.

00:05:13.360 --> 00:05:14.900
I wasn't able to make it in time.

00:05:16.020 --> 00:05:18.780
I promised that we would
run together someday.

00:05:19.660 --> 00:05:22.790
I wanted to run with her and
compete against her again.

00:05:23.430 --> 00:05:25.630
I can't help but regret that.

00:05:25.980 --> 00:05:28.810
In a way, regrets are a kind
of hope for the future.

00:05:29.220 --> 00:05:32.710
As long as you hold onto them, there's
a chance a twist of fate could lead to

00:05:33.170 --> 00:05:34.810
them being realized some day.

00:05:36.050 --> 00:05:37.710
Maybe you're right.

00:05:44.280 --> 00:05:47.280
Shocking Press Conference
Kitasan Black
Announces Retirement
from the Twinkle Series

00:05:49.930 --> 00:05:52.660
Upsy-daisy—ouch!

00:05:53.320 --> 00:05:56.290
I went and did it...

00:05:56.290 --> 00:05:58.800
Aw, I really went and did it.

00:05:59.890 --> 00:06:01.500
A-Are you okay?

00:06:01.500 --> 00:06:03.560
Oh, it's no big deal...

00:06:06.800 --> 00:06:09.180
You're a student at Tracen Academy?

00:06:09.180 --> 00:06:10.950
Yes! Starting in April.

00:06:13.950 --> 00:06:18.060
You just need to unload
these boxes, right? Let me help!

00:06:18.060 --> 00:06:20.060
No, no, I couldn't possibly...

00:06:20.060 --> 00:06:21.750
I don't mind at all!

00:06:21.750 --> 00:06:24.440
I'm pretty good at physical stuff!

00:06:24.440 --> 00:06:26.620
Okay, let's do this!

00:06:32.920 --> 00:06:36.660
You were a real lifesaver! Thanks, miss.

00:06:36.660 --> 00:06:39.050
There's something my dad used to say.

00:06:39.050 --> 00:06:41.520
When someone needs help, you help them.

00:06:41.520 --> 00:06:44.290
If someone is sad, you laugh by their side.

00:06:44.290 --> 00:06:47.670
That way, everyone can be happy and healthy!

00:06:47.670 --> 00:06:48.970
I see...

00:06:48.970 --> 00:06:50.800
Well, I'm heading off!

00:06:50.800 --> 00:06:53.490
Oh, wait a sec! What's your name, miss?

00:06:54.170 --> 00:06:56.430
I'm Kitasan Black.

00:06:59.690 --> 00:07:03.240
Kita-chan's retiring from
the Twinkle Series.

00:07:03.240 --> 00:07:06.190
Are you ever gonna stop moping?

00:07:06.680 --> 00:07:07.870
It's just...

00:07:07.870 --> 00:07:12.950
Kita-chan is going to be
racing for us two more times!

00:07:12.950 --> 00:07:17.210
Do you really wanna watch her with
that sorry look on your face?

00:07:19.190 --> 00:07:20.470
You're right.

00:07:20.780 --> 00:07:25.340
All we can really do is cheer for her with
the same energy that she helps us with.

00:07:25.340 --> 00:07:29.470
That's right! And if you get that, how
about you finish getting ready to open?

00:07:29.470 --> 00:07:32.190
Right! Okay, let's do this!

00:07:32.590 --> 00:07:36.100
Takeshi Greengrocers

00:07:33.890 --> 00:07:36.100
I went and did it!

00:07:44.610 --> 00:07:45.950
How many laps is this?

00:07:46.630 --> 00:07:47.910
Three.

00:07:49.800 --> 00:07:52.360
She used to be able to do that
without losing her breath.

00:07:53.030 --> 00:07:54.740
You're right.

00:07:55.400 --> 00:07:59.490
She's desperately struggling
against her own incoming decline.

00:07:59.950 --> 00:08:02.750
And the only way to do that is
with diligent, ordinary training.

00:08:03.130 --> 00:08:07.530
In that case, she'll be okay. Kita-chan's
got the diligence thing down to an art.

00:08:09.540 --> 00:08:10.750
Yeah.

00:08:15.510 --> 00:08:18.110
You're really fired up, Crown-chan.

00:08:18.110 --> 00:08:20.070
Well, I don't want to lose again.

00:08:21.260 --> 00:08:25.430
Before, at the Tennoushou,
I almost caught her.

00:08:25.430 --> 00:08:29.870
Next time will be revenge... or so I thought.

00:08:31.210 --> 00:08:35.290
Crown-san, you've raced
Kitasan Black-san six times

00:08:35.290 --> 00:08:38.280
since you were both in the Classics, right?

00:08:38.900 --> 00:08:42.600
We're from the same generation.
Rivals, but also friends.

00:08:43.020 --> 00:08:47.540
And when I heard she was going
to retire... I don't know how to put it.

00:08:48.420 --> 00:08:50.650
It's like finding out a kid is moving away

00:08:50.650 --> 00:08:52.650
right after they said, "See you tomorrow."

00:08:53.170 --> 00:08:54.650
Something like that.

00:08:55.730 --> 00:08:59.900
But seeing how she's working
so hard for her last two races

00:09:00.410 --> 00:09:02.870
has made me realize I should, too.

00:09:03.430 --> 00:09:04.670
You've got a point.

00:09:05.410 --> 00:09:06.860
Are you not entering, Dia?

00:09:07.530 --> 00:09:08.810
The Arima Kinen.

00:09:08.810 --> 00:09:12.570
I think it'll be your last
chance to run with Kitasan.

00:09:12.990 --> 00:09:15.190
If you get put on the fan ballot...

00:09:15.190 --> 00:09:19.610
I don't think I could put on
a very good race right now.

00:09:20.440 --> 00:09:22.340
Because of what happened at
the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe?

00:09:22.680 --> 00:09:23.700
Yeah...

00:09:24.050 --> 00:09:26.650
The turf and altitude differences

00:09:26.650 --> 00:09:30.070
made it feel like a different sport
altogether than in Japan.

00:09:30.070 --> 00:09:32.320
In order to win the Prix
de l'Arc de Triomphe,

00:09:32.320 --> 00:09:35.030
you need to be willing to abandon everything
you've built up until that point

00:09:35.030 --> 00:09:37.700
and start your training over from scratch.

00:09:38.210 --> 00:09:40.600
And even then, that's not
a guarantee you can win.

00:09:41.270 --> 00:09:47.780
What should I be doing? What should
I be looking toward as I run forward?

00:09:48.240 --> 00:09:52.330
Until I have an answer, I'm not
sure I can start moving on.

00:09:52.670 --> 00:09:55.040
Well, you can take your
time and think about it.

00:09:56.230 --> 00:09:59.820
I'm sure there's some stuff you
can only see when you stand still.

00:10:03.210 --> 00:10:05.170
Thank you, Crown-chan.

00:10:13.290 --> 00:10:15.300
Chevacchi, there you are!

00:10:16.980 --> 00:10:18.430
You need something?

00:10:18.430 --> 00:10:22.360
We're about to go get something
to eat. Do you want to join us?

00:10:22.360 --> 00:10:23.740
I'm fine.

00:10:23.740 --> 00:10:27.320
Aw, what's wrong, Chevacchi?!
Does your tummy hurt?

00:10:27.320 --> 00:10:28.930
It's not that!

00:10:28.930 --> 00:10:33.040
Right now, all of Cheval's
thoughts are focused on Kitasan.

00:10:33.040 --> 00:10:34.570
How'd you—

00:10:35.220 --> 00:10:38.240
Are you missing her? Or maybe sad?

00:10:40.680 --> 00:10:43.330
I'm honestly mad.

00:10:43.820 --> 00:10:47.710
When I heard Kitasan was quitting,
my reaction was, "Why?!"

00:10:48.570 --> 00:10:51.670
I've never really beaten her.

00:10:52.170 --> 00:10:55.230
And now she's going to just leave?

00:10:55.690 --> 00:10:57.830
I understand how you feel.

00:10:59.110 --> 00:11:03.030
When you think about them,
you're jealous and resentful.

00:11:03.460 --> 00:11:06.910
But you can't help but think about them, can't tear your eyes away...

00:11:07.270 --> 00:11:09.980
Your envy and admiration
get all mixed together,

00:11:10.410 --> 00:11:12.730
and it almost feels like infatuation.

00:11:13.990 --> 00:11:16.930
In my case, I never beat that person...

00:11:17.450 --> 00:11:21.740
But you've still got a chance. Two, in fact.

00:11:22.550 --> 00:11:23.610
Sis...

00:11:23.610 --> 00:11:24.870
She's right!

00:11:24.870 --> 00:11:26.800
More than me and even our sister,

00:11:26.800 --> 00:11:30.750
when things get really desperate, you've always
been the most focused, Chevacchi!

00:11:34.000 --> 00:11:36.710
Two more chances..

00:11:34.000 --> 00:11:38.000
Umamusume

00:11:34.000 --> 00:11:38.000
Pretty Derby

00:11:53.470 --> 00:11:57.790
Now that I think about it, I've never
been good at dealing with her type.

00:11:59.280 --> 00:12:01.780
Congratulations on enrolling

00:11:59.760 --> 00:12:03.720
She's so bright, and active, and sociable.

00:12:01.780 --> 00:12:04.130
Che... Cheval Grand.

00:12:04.130 --> 00:12:06.530
My goal is to win a G1 race.

00:12:04.330 --> 00:12:08.720
Nothing like me. Closer to the way
my big sister and Vivlos are.

00:12:06.820 --> 00:12:08.720
Nice to meet you.

00:12:08.720 --> 00:12:10.040
That's what she seemed like.

00:12:11.380 --> 00:12:12.910
I'm Kitasan Black!

00:12:14.170 --> 00:12:19.670
My goal is to be a strong,
glitzy horse girl like Tokai Teio!

00:12:19.670 --> 00:12:24.180
First up, I want to win all my races
before winning the Classic Triple Crown!

00:12:24.180 --> 00:12:25.840
It's nice to meet you all!

00:12:27.430 --> 00:12:31.210
She had this big dream,
and she was proud of it.

00:12:35.530 --> 00:12:39.460
She was tough, resilient, and strong.

00:12:39.460 --> 00:12:42.050
She had everything I wished I did.

00:12:42.630 --> 00:12:45.460
I was honestly so jealous.

00:12:50.860 --> 00:12:56.840
I tried hard, despite my losses,
but I was never able to do it like she did.

00:12:57.800 --> 00:13:04.300
She ran into her own hurdles too, but she
worked hard, so hard, and overcame them.

00:13:04.960 --> 00:13:06.550
Which is why I thought...

00:13:09.890 --> 00:13:11.210
I had to work hard too.

00:13:13.430 --> 00:13:15.060
Because I didn't want to lose to her.

00:13:18.580 --> 00:13:20.820
I wanted to win...

00:13:22.320 --> 00:13:26.320
Against the girl who was called
the strongest of our generation.

00:13:26.320 --> 00:13:27.550
I want to beat Kitasan Black!

00:13:28.320 --> 00:13:32.040
No matter how many times she
one-ups me, I won't give up.

00:13:32.990 --> 00:13:34.690
I can do it, too.

00:13:35.650 --> 00:13:39.330
I can work hard. As hard as she does.

00:13:39.630 --> 00:13:45.610
Work hard and get close,
and then closer, and then next time...

00:13:54.050 --> 00:13:57.910
I'll finally pass the person I've
seen in front of me all this time!

00:14:22.350 --> 00:14:24.240
We're here underneath an autumn sky,

00:14:24.240 --> 00:14:26.250
with the fanfare ringing
loud throughout the track.

00:14:26.250 --> 00:14:29.340
And soon the trademark domestic G1
race, the Japan Cup, will begin.

00:14:29.730 --> 00:14:32.080
And I imagine the spotlight
will be on Kitasan Black.

00:14:32.080 --> 00:14:35.930
Right. I'm sure there are many fans in the
stands who came to get a glimpse of her,

00:14:35.930 --> 00:14:38.350
now that she's announced her
retirement from the Twinkle Series.

00:14:38.350 --> 00:14:41.060
The horse girls make their way into the gate

00:14:41.060 --> 00:14:42.610
with looks that convey their determination.

00:14:42.830 --> 00:14:46.730
The most favored, Kitasan Black,
enters gate four.

00:14:47.150 --> 00:14:52.120
The players have assembled. And last
into the gate is number 17, Big Subject.

00:14:56.650 --> 00:14:58.550
And they're off.

00:14:58.550 --> 00:15:02.210
In the initial fight for the lead, number
four, Kitasan Black, is making her play.

00:15:03.910 --> 00:15:06.000
Hell yeah, good start!

00:15:06.000 --> 00:15:07.630
Looks like she's focused!

00:15:07.630 --> 00:15:09.510
Go!

00:15:09.510 --> 00:15:11.910
I can still see Kitasan in front of me.

00:15:12.840 --> 00:15:16.300
The same as usual. Kitasan
is pulling the rest of us.

00:15:16.770 --> 00:15:20.110
But I won't let her get away today.

00:15:20.520 --> 00:15:23.340
The Japan Cup tends to be
a high-level competition

00:15:23.340 --> 00:15:26.810
featuring both domestic and
foreign G1 horse girls.

00:15:26.810 --> 00:15:27.780
What brought this on?

00:15:27.780 --> 00:15:30.050
Not only that, but at 2,400 meters of turf,

00:15:30.050 --> 00:15:31.730
it's got a very orthodox
distance for the classics.

00:15:31.730 --> 00:15:34.400
In other words, it's the same distance as
other top-tier international turf races,

00:15:34.400 --> 00:15:36.290
like the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:15:36.290 --> 00:15:39.140
There have been times when shocking
speeds led to record times here,

00:15:39.140 --> 00:15:41.400
which requires high levels
of stamina in order to stay

00:15:41.400 --> 00:15:42.910
in contention with these tough conditions—

00:15:43.290 --> 00:15:44.360
What's wrong?

00:15:44.360 --> 00:15:47.490
Kitasan Black only has two races left.

00:15:48.390 --> 00:15:51.080
So we're going to burn every last
second into our memories.

00:15:52.840 --> 00:15:54.180
Good point.

00:15:52.840 --> 00:15:54.180
Good idea.

00:15:54.180 --> 00:15:58.100
The pace today has the first 1,000
meters cleared in 60.2 seconds.

00:15:58.100 --> 00:16:00.810
And setting that pace in
the lead is this runner!

00:16:00.810 --> 00:16:02.690
The festival girl, Kitasan Black!

00:16:02.690 --> 00:16:03.980
You can do it, Kita-chan!

00:16:03.980 --> 00:16:05.150
Come on!

00:16:05.390 --> 00:16:09.570
I couldn't manage in the Tennoushou...
but this time, I'm going to pass her!

00:16:09.570 --> 00:16:12.280
Crown-san! Fight!

00:16:12.280 --> 00:16:15.280
Kitasan Black is on the run,
with a lead of one and a half lengths.

00:16:15.530 --> 00:16:18.810
In second place is Mushamusha,
and in third is Toujours.

00:16:18.810 --> 00:16:21.810
On the inside, Cheval Grand
has moved into fourth.

00:16:21.810 --> 00:16:23.140
Go, Cheval!

00:16:23.140 --> 00:16:24.790
Hang in there, Chevacchi!

00:16:25.710 --> 00:16:27.080
Kitasan Black...

00:16:28.130 --> 00:16:30.300
I hate you.

00:16:30.730 --> 00:16:34.980
You've got the exact opposite personality
as me, and everyone loves you.

00:16:36.210 --> 00:16:40.890
There are always smiles and
energy all around you.

00:16:42.430 --> 00:16:46.580
And even with someone like me, you were
never shy about getting up close.

00:16:47.340 --> 00:16:49.690
We're down to the last 600 meters!

00:16:49.690 --> 00:16:51.690
Kitasan Black is still out
in front as they transition

00:16:51.690 --> 00:16:53.570
from the fourth corner into the straight!

00:16:53.860 --> 00:16:57.230
Kitasan Black is in the lead!
She's standing boldly on top!

00:16:57.820 --> 00:16:59.030
Whoa, there!

00:17:00.120 --> 00:17:01.940
And there she goes!

00:17:01.940 --> 00:17:04.080
It's Cheval Grand who emerges from the pack!

00:17:04.080 --> 00:17:06.620
She's champing at Kitasan Black's heels!

00:17:08.430 --> 00:17:12.170
Kitasan Black, I hate you.

00:17:13.210 --> 00:17:16.330
Whenever I see you running in front of me,

00:17:16.890 --> 00:17:21.930
it reminds me of how immature
and pitiful I am.

00:17:23.610 --> 00:17:29.420
It was so annoying and irritating...
but also brilliant.

00:17:31.730 --> 00:17:35.690
At some point, I couldn't
stop looking your way.

00:17:35.690 --> 00:17:38.280
Here comes Cheval Grand!
Cheval Grand is moving up!

00:17:38.280 --> 00:17:41.930
Kitasan Black, I hate you.

00:17:42.730 --> 00:17:45.870
It's because of you that I've come so far.

00:17:46.530 --> 00:17:51.640
Because you were there, I made
it to today without giving up.

00:17:52.420 --> 00:17:53.800
Kitasan Black...

00:17:54.290 --> 00:17:57.070
The truth is... I...

00:17:57.660 --> 00:17:59.470
I've always...

00:18:00.120 --> 00:18:03.660
loved you!

00:18:03.660 --> 00:18:05.410
Whoa! And she's gaining ground!

00:18:05.410 --> 00:18:08.390
Cheval Grand is showing
scorching acceleration!

00:18:08.390 --> 00:18:11.490
The gap between her and Kitasan
Black is gradually shrinking!

00:18:32.430 --> 00:18:34.070
It's Cheval Grand!

00:18:34.070 --> 00:18:35.460
Cheval Grand is in the lead!

00:18:35.460 --> 00:18:37.880
Kitasan Black has been passed for the lead!

00:18:37.880 --> 00:18:39.700
On the outside, Ay Tanri
is also on the attack!

00:18:39.700 --> 00:18:41.710
Will Kitasan Black fight back to the top?!

00:18:41.710 --> 00:18:43.450
But Cheval Grand persists!

00:18:43.450 --> 00:18:44.610
She's still in front!

00:18:44.610 --> 00:18:45.840
Cheval Grand in the lead!

00:18:45.840 --> 00:18:47.460
It's Cheval Grand!

00:18:47.460 --> 00:18:50.400
And Cheval Grand crosses
the goal in first place!

00:18:51.520 --> 00:18:53.480
With incredible competitors on her heels,

00:18:53.480 --> 00:18:57.810
she earns her first G1 victory
here at the Japan Cup!

00:18:58.200 --> 00:19:02.790
On her seventh attempt at a G1 race,
she has finally seized a win.

00:19:02.790 --> 00:19:04.330
Passing the evasive Kitasan Black,

00:19:04.330 --> 00:19:07.830
and outrunning Ay Tanri's
pursuit to clinch the race!

00:19:07.830 --> 00:19:12.330
This has been a grand race indeed,
and she has proven her mettle today!

00:19:12.330 --> 00:19:15.090
She really did it! Amazing, Cheval!

00:19:15.090 --> 00:19:19.450
Congrats, Chevacchi! Now we've all got G1 wins!

00:19:29.140 --> 00:19:29.740
I...

00:19:31.850 --> 00:19:33.280
I did it.

00:20:08.380 --> 00:20:10.270
Congratulations, Cheval-chan.

00:20:14.810 --> 00:20:16.270
Thank you, Kitasan.

00:20:19.740 --> 00:20:20.560
Kitasan...

00:20:22.050 --> 00:20:25.850
I'm going to do it. I'll become a
great horse girl that surpasses you.

00:20:30.850 --> 00:20:33.290
Nicely done! That was a great race!

00:20:33.290 --> 00:20:36.040
We'll be back for the next one, too!

00:20:36.370 --> 00:20:38.500
Good luck with the Arima Kinen!

00:20:38.500 --> 00:20:41.800
This will be the last time, so we'll make
sure to cheer for you with everything!

00:20:42.740 --> 00:20:44.090
The Arima Kinen...

00:20:46.130 --> 00:20:48.700
That's right. Next time is...

00:21:17.530 --> 00:21:18.560
Kita-chan...

00:21:20.400 --> 00:21:23.910
The concert's over. What are
you still doing here?

00:21:24.500 --> 00:21:25.940
I realized this would be

00:21:25.940 --> 00:21:29.270
my last time racing in the
Tokyo Racecourse for the Twinkle Series,

00:21:29.270 --> 00:21:31.550
so I wanted to take a good look at it.

00:21:32.180 --> 00:21:33.470
I see.

00:21:34.010 --> 00:21:36.130
This is where my debut race was, too.

00:21:36.660 --> 00:21:39.930
I can still remember how excited I was.

00:21:41.530 --> 00:21:46.220
And at the Derby... Dura-chan's
running was amazing.

00:21:46.700 --> 00:21:47.340
Yeah.

00:21:47.730 --> 00:21:53.800
And then the Fall Tennoushou, and the
Japan Cup... I ran a lot of G1 races here.

00:21:53.800 --> 00:21:54.750
Yeah...

00:21:55.500 --> 00:22:02.900
Hey, Dia-chan... remember when
I asked about how a last run must feel?

00:22:04.320 --> 00:22:07.000
I think I understand now.

00:22:07.450 --> 00:22:10.170
It's a really painful feeling.

00:22:11.320 --> 00:22:12.370
Kita-chan...

00:22:14.130 --> 00:22:16.690
I guess it really is over
after the next one.

00:22:19.130 --> 00:22:22.500
I sure hope I can win the Arima Kinen.

